Tahini Shortbread Sandwich Cookies

Cookie:
10 tbsp unsalted butter
3/4 c tahini stirred
2/3 c sugar
2 tsp kosher salt
1 1/2 c ap flour + more for dusting
1/4 c sesame seeds

Preheat the oven to 350F. In a medium bowl, combine the butter, tahini, sugar and salt. Using an electric hand mixer, beat the mixture until light and fluffy, 2 min. Add the flour and mix until a dough comes together. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 min.

Ganache
2 c (12oz) semisweet chocolate chips
1/2 c tahini
1/4 c honey
2 tsp kosher salt
1 1/2 c heavy cream

In a medium bowl, combine the chocolate chips, tahini, honey and kosher salt. In a small saucepan, bring the heavy cream to a simmer, then pour the cream over the chocolate mixture. Let sit for 2 min, then whisk until smooth. Let cool completely then transfer to a piping bag fitted with a large star tip.

Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough out into a 14" circle, 1/3" thick. With a 2 1/4" round cutter, cut out 40 circles, rerolling scraps as needed. Transfer to the prepared baking sheets, 1" apart, and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake until lightly golden, 18-20 min. Pipe 3 tbsp coole ganache onto half of the cookies, then top with the remaining cookies to sandwich together and serve.

